title: Barbell Curl
steps: Hold the barbell using an underhand grip, hands about shoulder-width, you can make slight adjustments depending on your comfort.
Keep your upper arms steady as you curl the barbell.
Elevate the barbell until your biceps are completely contracted, and the bar reaches your shoulders.
Pause briefly and squeeze your biceps.
Lower the barbell slowly to the start position controlling the decent with your biceps.

title: Dumbbell Curl
steps: Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your arms straight down and palms facing your body.
Without moving your upper arms, curl both dumbbells up by contracting your biceps.
As you raise the dumbbells, rotate your palms to face up.
Lift until the dumbbells are at shoulder level.
Pause briefly and squeeze the your bicep.
Lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position.

title: Dumbbell Hammer Curl
steps: Hold the dumbbells in each hand using a neutral grip (palms facing your body).
Stand with your feet at shoulder-width distance.
Keeping your upper arms stable, raise the dumbbells towards your shoulders using your biceps.
Pause briefly at the top and squeeze your bicep.
Gradually lower dumbbells to the start position.

title: Kettlebell Goblet Curl
steps: Hold the Kettlebell with both hands, cupping the round part (bell).
Stand with your feet hip-width apart, keeping an upright posture.
Start with the Kettlebell in front of your hips.
Keeping your upper arms stable, raise the dumbbells towards your shoulders using your biceps.
Gradually lower the kettlebell back to the starting position, maintaining controlled movement throughout.

title: Kettlebell Concentration Curl
steps: Sit on a bench with your legs spread apart.
Hold the kettlebell between your legs, with your elbow on your inner thigh, your arm extended towards the ground, and your palms facing your opposite leg.
Curl the kettlebell towards your shoulder.
Pause briefly at top of the curl and squeeze your bicep.
Slowly lower kettlebell back down to the starting position, maintaining control.

title: Kettlebell Preacher Curl
steps: Stand behind a bench, with your chest leaning over the edge of the bench.
With one arm resting on the bench, hold the kettlebell, bending the arm at the elbow.
Lower your arm using the bench as a guide, keeping your forearm straight.
Return to the starting position and repeat.

title: Kettlebell Single Arm Curl
steps: Stand upright, holding a kettlebell in each hand with an underhand grip(palms facing outwards).
Keep your arm close to your body and your elbow stationary.
Curl the kettlebell upward by flexing your bicep.
Pause at the top of the curl and squeeze your bicep.
Gradually lower the kettlebell back down to the starting position.

title: Band Bayesian Curl
steps: Attach band to a low anchor point. Point your palms straight forward.
Flex your elbow until you feel your biceps contract. Then fully extend elbows.

title: Band Bayesian Hammer Curl
steps: Attach band to a low anchor point. Use a neutral grip.
Flex your elbow until you feel your biceps contract. Then fully extend elbows.

title: Band Bayesian Reverse Curl
steps: Attach band to a low anchor point. . Point your palms toward your thighs.
Flex your elbow until you feel your biceps contract. Then fully extend elbows.

title: Dumbbell Reverse Curl
steps: Hold dumbbells with palms facing down (reverse grip).
Stand with feet shoulder-width apart.
Keeping your upper arms steady, curl dumbbells toward shoulders.
Squeeze biceps briefly at the top of the curl.
Lower dumbbells back to start in a controlled manner.

title: Barbell Reverse Curl
steps: Hold the barbell with a reverse grip (palms facing down), and your hands about shoulder-width apart or what feels comfortable to you.
Keep upper elbows close to your body throughout the movement.
Curl the barbell towards your shoulders, engaging your biceps.
Pause at the top briefly and squeeze your biceps.
Lower the barbell down to the starting position in a controlled manner.

title: Incline Dumbbell Hammer Curl
steps: Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle and sit on it.
Hold a dumbbell in each hand with a neutral grip (palms facing your body).
Start with arms extended down.
Curl the dumbbells upward while keeping upper arms still. Palms facing each other throughout the movement.
Briefly pausing at the top and focusing on squeezing your biceps.
Lower the dumbbells back down to starting in a controlled movement.

title: Incline Dumbbell Reverse Curl
steps: Set up an incline bench at around a 45-degree angle and sit on it.
Hold a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip (palms facing down).
Begin with arms fully extended, hanging down naturally.
Curl the dumbbells upward while keeping your upper arms steady and elbows close to your body.
Pause briefly at the top, and focus on squeezing your biceps, and forearm muscles.
Lower the dumbbells back down in a controlled manner.

title: Incline Dumbbell Zottman Curl
steps: Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle and sit on it.
Hold a dumbbell in each hand with palms facing up (underhand grip).
Start with arms fully extended, hanging naturally.
Curl the dumbbells upward while keeping upper arms steady, palms facing up.
Once you reach the top, rotate your wrists, so palms face down (overhand grip).
Lower the dumbbells to the start with controlled movement.
Rotate the dumbbells to underhand grip and repeat.

title: Dumbbell Standing Single Arm Preacher Curl
steps: Stand behind an angled preacher curl bench, or angle a bench at 45-degrees.
Hold a dumbbell in one hand with an underhand grip (palm facing up)and elbow resting on the bench.
Position your upper arms against the pad and let your arms hang fully extended.
Curl the dumbbell upward while keeping upper arms against the pad.
At the top of the movement pause briefly and squeeze your bicep.
Lower the dumbbell back down in a controlled manner, maintaining proper form.

title: Dumbbell Single Arm Spider Curl
steps: Lie facedown on an incline bench, holding a dumbbell in one hand with an underhand grip (palm facing up).
Let your arm to hang down naturally off the bench.
Curl the dumbbell upward while keeping your upper arm stationary.
Squeeze your bicep at the top of the movement.
Lower the dumbbell back down in a controlled manner.

title: Dumbbell Spider Curl
steps: Lie facedown on an incline bench set at a 45-degree slight angle.
Hold a dumbbell in each hand with an underhand grip (palms facing up).
Allow your arms to hang straight down naturally.
Curl the dumbbells upward while keeping your upper arms stationary.
Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, then lower the dumbbells back down in a controlled manner.

title: Dumbbell Twisting Curl
steps: Stand upright with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your body.
Keep your upper arms stationary and your elbows close to your torso.
Curl the dumbbells, rotating your wrists as you lift.
As you curl, turn your palms to face your shoulders at the top of the movement.
Slowly lower the dumbbells back down while rotating your wrists back to the starting position.

title: Plate Bicep Curl
steps: Stand straight and hold a weight plate by its sides.
Start with your arms extended and plate in front of your hips. Keep your upper arms close to your body.
Curl the plate using your biceps.
At the top, pause briefly and squeeze your biceps.
Lower the weight plate in a controlled manner to the initial position.

title: Plate Curl To Press
steps: Stand straight and grasp a weight plate by its sides holding it in front of your hips.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. Keep your upper arms close to your body.
Curl the plate using your biceps towards your shoulders, keep your upper arms close to your body.
Once the plate is at shoulder level, smoothly transition into an overhead press by pushing the plate upward.
Lower the plate back down to shoulder level, then reverse the motion by curling it back down to the starting position.

title: Plate Curl To Press To Tricep Extension
steps: Stand straight and grasp a weight plate by its sides holding it in front of your hips.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. Keep your upper arms close to your body.
Curl the plate toward your shoulders, engaging your biceps.
Transition smoothly into an overhead press, pushing the plate upward.
From the overhead position, bend your elbows to lower the plate behind your head, performing a tricep extension.
Extend your arms back up to the press and reverse the movement back to the starting position to complete 1 rep.

title: Squat Hold Bicep Curl
steps: Hold a weight plate by its side.
Sit in a squat.
While holding the squat, curl the weight plate toward your shoulders using your biceps.
Lower the weight plate back down while maintaining the squat position.

title: Band High Curl
steps: Attach a resistance band securely to an anchor point above your head.
Stand facing the anchor point with your feet hip-width apart and your elbows at chest level or slightly above.
Hold the band with an underhand grip, arms extended.
Curl your hands towards your forehead using your biceps.
Pause briefly and squeeze your biceps.
Slowly lower your hands and the band back down to the starting position.

title: Band High Hammer Curl
steps: Attach a resistance band securely to an anchor point above your head.
Stand facing the anchor point with your feet hip-width apart and your elbows at chest level.
Hold the band with an neutral grip (palms facing each other), arms extended.
Curl your hands towards your forehead using your biceps.
Pause briefly and squeeze your biceps.
Slowly lower your hands and the band back down to the starting position.

title: Band High Reverse Curl
steps: Attach a resistance band securely to an anchor point above your head.
Stand facing the anchor point with your feet hip-width apart and your elbows at chest level.
Hold the band with an overhand grip (palms facing down), arms extended.
Curl your hands towards your forehead using your biceps.
Pause briefly and squeeze your biceps.
Slowly lower your hands and the band back down to the starting position.

title: Band Bicep Curl
steps: Place the resistance band under the balls of your feet and stand with your feet about hip-width apart.
Hold the resistance band handles with an underhand grip (palms facing up), arms extended down.
Keep your upper arms close to your torso and stationary throughout the movement.
Curl your hands and the band handles upwards towards your shoulders by bending your elbows and keeping your upper arm stationary.
Gradually lower your hands and the band back down to the starting position.

title: Band Reverse Bicep Curl
steps: Place the resistance band under the balls of your feet and stand with your feet about hip-width apart.
Hold the resistance band handles with an overhand grip (palms facing down), arms extended down.
Keep your upper arms close to your torso and stationary throughout the movement.
Curl your hands and the band handles upwards towards your shoulders by bending your elbows and keeping your upper arm stationary.
Gradually lower your hands and the band back down to the starting position.

title: Dumbbell Concentration Curl
steps: Sit on a bench, holding a dumbbell in one hand with your legs spread.
Lean and place your elbow against your inner thigh with your arm extended.
Curl the dumbbell upwards without moving your upper arm or your elbow.
Pause briefly at the top and squeeze your bicep.
Lower the dumbbell back to the starting position.

title: Barbell Unilateral Landmine Row
steps: Place one end of a barbell in a landmine attachment or secure it in a corner.
Stand with your feet hip-width apart, facing the barbell.
Bend at the hips and knees to lower your torso until it is almost parallel to the ground.
Hinge at the hip, engage your core,  with one hand grasp the free end of the barbell with a neutral grip (palm facing your body) and your hands extended.
Row the barbell towards your torso without flaring your body.
Pause briefly at the top squeezing your shoulder blades.
Lower the barbell back to the starting position to complete the movement.

title: Chin Ups
steps: Hang from a pull-up bar with your palms facing towards you, hands shoulder-width apart or what feels comforatble to you.
Pull your body upward by bending your elbows, bringing your chin above the bar.
Pause briefly at the top, focusing on using your back and biceps muscles.
Lower your body back down in a controlled manner to the starting position.

title: Band Kneeling Single Arm Lat Pulldown
steps: Attach a resistance band overhead to a sturdy anchor point.
Kneel on the floor, facing the anchor, with the knee opposite to the working arm down.
Grasp the resistance band handle with the working hand using a neutral grip (palm facing your body) and your arm extended forward.
Pull the handle down towards your hip, pulling your elbow back and keeping it close to your body.
Slowly return to the standing postion the handle back up, maintaining control throughout the movement.

title: Barbell Single Arm Extended Landmine Row
steps:
Place one end of a barbell into a landmine attachment or secure it in a corner.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, hinge at the hips.
Hold the end of the barbell with a neutral grip (palms facing your torso) and your arm extended.
Keep your back straight and core engaged as you row the barbell towards your torso.
Lower the barbell back down in a controlled manner to complete the movement.

title: Meadows Row
steps: Set up a barbell in a landmine attachment or securely anchor it in a corner.
Stand sideways to the barbell (barbell should be parallel to your chest) and your feet staggered and one foot in front of the other.
Hinge at the hip, hold the barbell handle with an overhand grip (palm facing down) with hand opposite to your forward foot.
Row the barbell towards your torso, squeezing your back muscles
Slowly return to the starting position.

title: Pendlay Row
steps: Stand with your feet hip-width apart and grip the barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width.
Hinge your hips and knees, keeping your back flat.
Starting with the barbell on the floor and your arms extended.
Pull the barbell up towards your lower chest.
Lower the barbell back to the floor slowly.

title: Pronated Bent Over Barbell Row
steps: Stand with your feet about shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width.
Bend at your hips while keeping your back straight, maintaining a slight bend in your knees.
Keep your upper body parallel to the floor, allowing the barbell to hang at arm's length but not touch the floor.
Pull the barbell towards your lower ribcage by retracting your shoulder blades and bending your elbows.
Lower the barbell back down to the starting position slowly.

title: Supinated Pendlay Row
steps: Place a loaded barbell on the floor and stand with your feet hip-width apart.
Hinge at the hips, grip the barbell with an underhand grip (palms facing up), hands slightly wider than shoulder-width with the barbell next to your shins.
Pull the barbell up towards your lower chest by squeezing your shoulder blades together and pulling your elbows back.
Lower the barbell back to the floor in a controlled manner.

title: Supinated Bent Over Row
steps:
Stand with your feet about shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell with an underhand grip (palms facing up), hands slightly wider than shoulder-width.
Bend at your hips while keeping your back straight, your core braced, and your knees slightly bent.
Keep your upper body at an angle to the floor, allowing the barbell to hang in front of you at arm's length.
Pull the barbell towards your lower ribcage by retracting your shoulder blades and bending your elbows.
Lower the barbell back down to the starting position in a controlled manner.

title: Alternating Dumbbell Pendlay Row
steps: Stand with your feet about hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand.
Hinge at your hips, bend your knees, keeping your back straight, and brace your core.
Let the dumbbells rest on the floor with your arms fully extended.
Pull one dumbbell towards your lower ribcage by retracting your shoulder blade and bending your elbow while keeping the other arm extended.
Lower the dumbbell back down and repeat the row with the opposite arm.
Alternate sides while maintaining proper form throughout the movement.

title: Single Arm Dumbbell Row
steps: Begin by placing a dumbbell on the floor next to a bench.
Stand next to the bench, slightly bend your knees, and place one hand and one knee on the bench.
With your free hand, grasp the dumbbell with a neutral grip (palm facing your body).
Keep your back straight and your core engaged as you pull the dumbbell towards your hip by bending your elbow.
Lower the dumbbell back to the starting position.

title: Dumbell Incline Bench Row
steps: Set an incline bench to about a 45-degree angle and place two dumbbells at the base of the bench.
Lie face down on the incline bench, holding a dumbbell in each hand with a neutral grip (palms facing your body).
Allow your arms to hang down naturally towards the floor.
Pull the dumbbells towards your hip by bending your elbows, squeezing your shoulder blades together.
Lower the dumbbells back down in a controlled manner to the starting position while maintaining proper form throughout the movement.

title: Dumbbell Pendlay Row
steps: Stand with your feet about hip-width apart and slightly bend your knees.
Hinge at your hips while keeping your back straight.
Grasp the dumbbells with an neutral grip (palms facing each other), one in each hand, your arms fully extended so the dumbbells are on the floor.
Pull the dumbbells towards your hip by retracting your shoulder blades and bending your elbows, then lower them back down in a controlled manner to the floor.

title: Dumbbell One Arm Row
steps: Stand next to the bench with your feet about hip-width apart
Bend at your hips, keeping your back flat and your chest up, and place the hand opposite the working arm on the bench for support.
Grasp the dumbbell with the working hand using an neutral grip (palm facing your opposit hand).
Pull the dumbbell towards your hip by retracting your shoulder blade and bending your elbow
Lower it back down in a controlled manner to the starting position.

title: Dumbbell Knee Supported Single Arm Row
steps: Start by getting into a staggered stance.
Hinge at the hip and place your non-working elbow on your front knee for support.
Grasp the dumbbell with the working hand using a neutral grip (palm facing your opposite hand) and letting it extend down fully.
Pull the dumbbell towards your hip by retracting your shoulder blade and bending your elbow
Lower it back down in a controlled manner to the starting position.

title: Plate Pinch Row
steps: Hold a weight plate on each hand with your fingertips.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and a slight bend in your knees.
Hinge at your hips, maintaining a flat back, and let the weight plates hang at arm's length in front of you.
Pull the weight plates towards your lower ribcage by retracting your shoulder blades and bending your elbows.
Lower the weight plates back down in a controlled manner.

title: Lawnmower Row
steps: Begin with a dumbbell placed on the floor to the side of your feet.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, get into a lunge position with your back leg the same as the working arm.
Bend your hips and place the palm of your non-working arm on your front knee for support.
Hold the dumbbell with a neutral grip (palf facing your opposite leg) and let it hang down freely.
Pull the dumbbell upward and backward in a rowing motion, leading with your elbow and retracting your shoulder blade.
Lower the dumbbell back down in a controlled manner to the starting position.
Repeat on the other side.

title: Dumbbell Knee Lawnmower Row
steps: Stand with feet staggered and one hand on your knee. Hold a dumbbell in the opposing hand.
Hinge forward at the hips, keeping the back flat, and eyes facing forward. The weight should hang directly below the shoulders.
Start with an overhand grip, as you pull rotate the dumbbell. When your upper arm reaches your side your palm should be facing forward.

title: Supinated Dumbbell Row
steps: Stand with your feet about hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with an underhand grip (palms facing forward).
Pull the dumbbells towards your lower ribcage by retracting your shoulder blades and bending your elbows.
Let your arms hang freely, maintain an underhand grip, and then pull your elbow joint straight back toward the ceiling.
Lower the dumbbells back down in a controlled manner to the starting position.

title: Bench Press
steps: Lie flat on a bench with your feet firmly on the floor, eyes aligned with the barbell.
Grip the barbell slightly wider than shoulder-width apart, hands facing forward or slightly angled.
Unrack the barbell and lower it to your chest.
Push the barbell back up, extending your arms while maintaining control.
Repeat the movement for the desired number of reps, then rack the barbell back onto the supports.

title: Dips
steps: Place two sturdy boxes or platforms parallel to each other.
Position yourself between the boxes, placing your palms on each firmly.
Lift your body up by straightening your arms, locking out your elbows.
Lower your body by bending your elbows, keeping your torso upright and your legs slightly bent.
Continue the descent until your shoulders are just below your elbows, then push your body back up to the starting position.

title: Dumbbell Incline Fly
steps: Set an incline bench at a moderate angle (around 30-45 degrees).
Lie on the bench with a dumbbell in each hand, arms extended, and palms facing each other.
Keep a slight bend in your elbows throughout the movement.
Lower the dumbbells out to the sides in a wide arc, feeling a stretch in your chest.
Bring the dumbbells back up, squeezing your chest muscles at the top, then repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

title: Incline Bench Press
steps: Set an incline bench at a desired angle (usually around 30-45 degrees).
Lie on the bench with your feet flat on the floor and your back, shoulders, and head in contact with the bench.
Grip the barbell slightly wider than shoulder-width, with palms facing forward or slightly angled.
Unrack the barbell and lower it to your chest while keeping your elbows.
Push the barbell back up, extending your arms while maintaining control. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then rack the barbell.

title: Kettlebell Chest Press
steps: Lie on your back on a bench or the floor, holding a kettlebell in each hand.
Bend your elbows and position your upper arms on the ground (or inline with your chest if using a bench), with your forearms perpendicular to the floor.
Press the kettlebells upward by extending your arms while maintaining control.
Lower the kettlebells back down to chest level by bending your elbows.
Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, focusing on engaging your chest muscles.

title: Single Arm Kettlebell Fly
steps: Lie on your back on a bench or the floor, holding a kettlebell in one hand.
Extend your arm with a slight bend in your elbow and hold the kettlebell above your chest.
Lower the kettlebell out to the side in a wide arc, feeling a stretch in your chest.
Bring the kettlebell back up to the starting position by squeezing your chest muscles.
Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions on one side, then switch to the other arm.

title:
Kettlebell Single Arm Chest 
Press
steps: Lie on your back on a bench or the floor, holding a kettlebell in one hand.
Bend your elbow and position your upper arm on the ground (or inline with your chest if using a bench), with your forearm perpendicular to the floor.
Press the kettlebell upward by extending your arm while maintaining control.
Lower the kettlebell back down to chest level by bending your elbow.
Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions on one side, then switch to the other arm.

title: Kettlebell Walkover Pushup
steps: Start in a pushup position with your hands on the kettlebell and the other on the ground with both arms full extended.
Perform a pushup, lowering your chest towards the ground while maintaining a straight body.
After pushing back up, lift one hand off the kettlebell and move it to the opposite side.
Lift the other hand off the ground and move it to the kettlebell.
Perform another pushup with your hands on the opposite kettlebell handles. Repeat the walkover pattern in subsequent repetitions.

title: Push Up
steps: Start in a plank position, with your hands placed slightly wider than shoulder-width apart on the floor.
Keep your body in a straight line from head to heels, engaging your core muscles.
Lower your body towards the floor by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your sides.
Continue lowering until your chest is just above the ground or as far as comfortable.
Push back up by extending your arms, returning to the starting plank position.

title: Incline Push Up
steps: Position yourself facing an elevated surface, such as a bench, chair or a sturdy platform.
Place your hands on the elevated surface slightly wider than shoulder-width apart.
Walk your feet back until you are in a push up position.
Lower your chest towards the elevated surface by bending your elbows.
Push back up to the starting position by extending your arms.

title: Decline Push Up
steps: Position yourself with your back towards an elevated surface, like a bench or a platform.
Get into a push up position keeping your hands on the floor slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and the tips of your feet on the platform.
Lower your chest towards the floor by bending your elbows.
Push back up to the starting position by extending your arms.

title: Band Single Arm Fly
steps: Attach a resistance band securely to a fixed anchor point at chest level.
Hold the resistance band handle with one hand and step sideways until you feel tension in the band.
Extend your arm across your body using your pec, keeping a slight bend in your elbow.
Slowly bring your arm back to the starting position, feeling the stretch in your pecs.
Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions on one side, then switch to the other arm.

title: Band Single Arm Chest Press
steps: Attach a resistance band securely to a fixed anchor point at chest level behind.
Hold the resistance band handle with one hand and and step forward until you feel tension in the band.
Extend your arm forward completely using your chest.
Slowly bring your arm back to the starting position, controlling the motion with your chest.
Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions on one side, then switch to the other arm.

title: Resistance Band Pushup
steps: Get into a pushup position while looping a resistance band across your upper back, holding the ends in each hand.
Do a regular pushup.
While pushing back up, you should feel a tension in the band.

title: Barbell Floor Press
steps: Lie on the floor with your knees bent and feet flat, holding a barbell with an overhand grip.
Your hands should be slightly wider than shoulder-width apart.
Lower the barbell to your chest by bending your elbows.
Keep your upper arms in contact with the floor.
Push the barbell back up to the starting position by extending your arms.

title: Hooklying Bench Press
steps: Lie on a bench with your back flat, your knees bent and your feet flat on the bench.
Hold a barbell with an overhand grip and position your hands slightly wider than should width apart.
Unrack the barbell and lower it to your chest without flaring your elbows out.
Push the barbell back up using your pecs in a controlled manner.

title: Larsen Bench Press
steps: Lie on a bench with your back flat, straighten your legs and lift your feet off the floor.
Hold a barbell with an overhand grip and position your hands slightly wider than should width apart.
Unrack the barbell and lower it to your chest without flaring your elbows out.
Push the barbell back up using your pecs in a controlled manner.

title: Spoto Press
steps: Lie down with your back on the bench.
Unrack the barbell and hold it above your chest with arms extended.
Lower the barbell to your chest but stop just a couple of inches above your chest ("Spoto" position).
Pause briefly engaging your muscles.
Push the barbell back up to the starting position by extending your arms while maintaining control.

title: Dumbbell Bench Press
steps: Lie on a flat bench with your feet on the floor, and a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip.
Start with your arms extended and the dumbbells inline with your chest.
Keep your elbows at around a 45-degree angle from your sides.
Lower the dumbbells towards your chest by bending your elbows.
Push the dumbbells back up to the starting position by extending your arms while maintaining control.

title: Dumbbell Chest Fly
steps: Lie on a flat bench with your feet on the floor, and a dumbbell in each hand with an neutral grip (palms facing each other).
Start with your arms extended in front of you and the dumbbells inline with your chest and a slight bend in your elbows.
Lower the dumbbells out to the sides in a wide arc, feeling a stretch in your chest.
Keep a slight bend in your elbows throughout the movement.
Bring the dumbbells back up to the starting position by squeezing your chest muscles.

title: Decline Alternating Dumbbell Press
steps: Lie on a decline bench with your head lower than your hips, holding a dumbbell in each hand with an over hand grip.
Start with your arms extended above your chest.
Lower the dumbbells towards your chest by bending your elbows.
Keep your elbows at around a 45-degree angle from your body.
Push the dumbbells back up to the starting position by extending your arms while maintaining control.

title: Dumbbell Decline Bench Press
steps: Lie on a decline bench with your head lower than your hips, holding a dumbbell in each hand with an over hand grip.
Start with your arms extended above your chest.
Lower both dumbbells simultaneously towards your chest by bending your elbows.
Keep your elbows at around a 45-degree angle from your body.
Push the dumbbells back up to the starting position by extending your arms while maintaining control.

title: Dumbbell Decline Chest Fly
steps: Lie on a decline bench with your head lower than your hips, holding a dumbbell in each hand with a neutral grip (palms facing each other).
Start with your arms extended above your chest and with a slight bend in your elbows.
Lower the dumbbells out to the sides in a wide arc, feeling a stretch in your chest.
Keep a slight bend in your elbows throughout the movement.
Bring the dumbbells back up to the starting position by squeezing your chest muscles.

title: Dumbbell Decline Guillotine Bench Press
steps: Lie on a decline bench with your head lower than your hips, holding a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip.
Start with your arms extended, dumbbells slightly above your chest, closer to your neck.
Lower the dumbbells towards your neck, allowing your elbows to move out to the sides.
Press the dumbbells back up to the starting position by extending your arms while maintaining control.

title: Dumbbell Decline Hammer Press
steps: Lie on a decline bench at the desired angle (head lower than hips), and have a dumbbell in each hand.
Hold both dumbbells at shoulder level with your palms facing each other (neutral grip) and your arms extended fully.
Keep your elbows close to your body throughout the movement.
Lower the dumbbells down towards your chest by bending your elbows.
Press the dumbbells back towards the starting position.

title: Dumbbell Decline Single Arm Press
steps: Lie on a decline bench at the desired angle (head lower than hips), and have a dumbbell in each hand.
Hold both dumbbells at chest level using an overhand grip and your arms extended fully.
Slowly lower one dumbbell towards your chest by bending your elbow.
Keep your elbow at a 45 degree angle to your body as you bend it.
Hold the dumbbell in the opposite hand static throughout the movement.
Press the dumbbells back towards the starting position.
Repeat the movement in the opposite hand.

title: Decline Dumbbell Squeeze Press
steps: Set a bench at a decline and lie with your head lower than your hips and have a dumbbell in each hand.
Hold the dumbbells at chest level with palms facing each other.
Squeeze the dumbbells together throughout the movement and press them upwards with your chest.
Extend your arms fully at the top of the movement, maintaining the squeeze.
Lower the dumbbells back down to your chest, maintaining the squeeze.

title: Dumbbell Guillotine Bench Press
steps: Lie on a flat bench holding a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip.
Start with your arms extended, dumbbells slightly above your chest, closer to your neck.
Lower the dumbbells towards your neck, allowing your elbows to move out to the sides.
Press the dumbbells back up to the starting position by extending your arms while maintaining control.

title: Dumbbell Guillotine Incline Bench Press
steps: Lie on an inclined bench with your head higher than your hips, holding a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip.
Start with your arms extended, dumbbells slightly above your chest, closer to your neck.
Lower the dumbbells towards your neck, allowing your elbows to move out to the sides.
Press the dumbbells back up to the starting position by extending your arms while maintaining control.

title: Incline Dumbbell Bench Press
steps: Set an incline bench at a desired angle (usually around 30-45 degrees).
Sit on the bench and hold a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder level, using an overhand grip.
Press the dumbbells up while keeping your wrists aligned with your shoulders.
Extend your arms fully at the top of the movement.
Lower the dumbbells back down to shoulder level.

title: Dumbbell Incline Chest Fly
steps: Set an incline bench at a moderate angle (around 30-45 degrees).
Lie on the bench with a dumbbell in each hand, arms extended, and palms facing each other.
Keep a slight bend in your elbows throughout the movement.
Lower the dumbbells out to the sides in a wide arc, feeling a stretch in your chest.
Bring the dumbbells back up, squeezing your chest muscles at the top, then repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

title: Dumbbell Pronated Chest Fly
steps: Lie on a flat bench holding a dumbbell in each hand with a pronated (overhand) grip.
Extend both dumbbells in front of you with a slight bend in your elbows.
Lower the dumbbells out to the sides in a wide arc, feeling a stretch in your chest.
Bring the dumbbells back up, squeezing your chest muscles at the top, then repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

title: Dumbbell Pronated Incline Chest Fly
steps: Set an incline bench at a moderate angle (around 30-45 degrees).
Lie on the bench with a dumbbell in each hand, arms extended, and palms in a pronated (overhand) grip.
Keep a slight bend in your elbows throughout the movement.
Lower the dumbbells out to the sides in a wide arc, feeling a stretch in your chest.
Slowly bring back the dumbbells to the starting position be squeezing your chest.

title: Dumbbell Hammer Press
steps: Lie on a flat bench with a dumbbell in each hand.
Hold both dumbbells at shoulder level with your palms facing each other (neutral grip) and your arms extended fully.
Keep your elbows close to your body throughout the movement.
Lower the dumbbells down towards your chest by bending your elbows.
Press the dumbbells back towards the starting position.

title: Dumbbell Incline Hammer Press
steps: Lie on an inclined bench at the desired angle (head higher than hips), and have a dumbbell in each hand.
Hold both dumbbells at shoulder level with your palms facing each other (neutral grip) and your arms extended fully.
Keep your elbows close to your body throughout the movement.
Lower the dumbbells down towards your chest by bending your elbows.
Press the dumbbells back towards the starting position.

title: Dumbbell Squeeze Press
steps: Set a bench at a decline and lie with your head lower than your hips and have a dumbbell in each hand.
Hold the dumbbells at chest level with palms facing each other.
Squeeze the dumbbells together throughout the movement and press them upwards with your chest.
Extend your arms fully at the top of the movement, maintaining the squeeze.
Lower the dumbbells back down to your chest, maintaining the squeeze.

title: Burpee
steps: Begin by standing with your feet at hip-width distance.
Transition into a squat and place your hands on the ground before you.
Now transition into a plank by kicking your feet back.
Do a pushup.
Jump your feet back towards your hands and jump upright reaching your hands up into the air.

title: Band Chest Fly
steps: Attach a resistance band securely to a fixed anchor point at chest level.
Stand facing away from the anchor point, holding a handle in each hand using a neutral grip (palms facing each other).
Extend your arms forward at chest level, with a slight bend in your elbows.
Open your arms out to the sides in a wide arc, feeling a stretch in your chest.
Bring your arms back to the starting position by squeezing your chest muscles.

title: Band Chest Press
steps: Attach a resistance band securely to a fixed anchor point at chest level.
Stand facing away from the anchor point, holding a handle in each hand.
Position your hands at chest level with your elbows bent.
Push the handles forward until your arms are fully extended, engaging your chest muscles.
Slowly retract your arms back to the starting position in a controlled manner.

title: Band Pronated Chest Fly
steps: Attach a resistance band securely to a fixed anchor point at chest level.
Stand facing away from the anchor point, holding a handle in each hand using a pronated (palms facing down) grip.
Position your hands at chest level with your elbows bent.
Push the handles forward until your arms are fully extended, engaging your chest muscles.
Slowly retract your arms back to the starting position in a controlled manner.

title: Deficit Plate Pushup
steps: Place two weight plates on the floor, shoulder-width apart, with their flat sides facing up.
Assume a push-up position with your hands on the weight plates.
Lower your chest towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping your elbows close to your body.
Keep going until your upper arms travel past your body.
Push back up to the starting position by extending your arms while maintaining control.

title: Plate Bridge Chest Press
steps: Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor, holding a weight plate against your chest.
Position the weight plate comfortably against your chest using both hands.
Using your glutes and hamstrings, lift your hips off the ground, creating a straight line from your shoulders to your knees.
While maintaining the glute bridge position, press the weight plate upward, extending your arms fully.
Lower the weight plate back to your chest. Repeat the movement while keeping your hips elevated throughout the exercise.

title: Dumbbell Elevated Pushup
steps: Place two dumbbells on the floor parallel to each other, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart.
Assume a push-up position with your hands on the dumbbells.
Lower your chest towards the ground by bending your elbows.
Push back up to the starting position by extending your arms while maintaining control.

title: Pushup Renegade Row
steps: Place two dumbbells on the floor parallel to each other, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart.
Assume a push-up position with your hands on the dumbbells.
Do a push up.
In the plank position, row one dumbbell or kettlebell towards your hip, retracting your shoulder blade and keeping your elbow close to your body.
Lower the weight back to the ground, then row the other dumbbell in a similar manner.

title: Dumbbell Alternating Chest Press
steps: Lie on a flat bench, holding a dumbbell in each hand using an overhand grip.
Position the dumbbells at chest level with both arms fully extended out.
Lower one dumbbell down to chest level slowly without moving the opposite arm.
Push the dumbbell back to the starting position.
Repeat this movement on the opposite hand.
Continue alternating between the two dumbbells.

title: Barbell Squat
steps: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, with the barbell racked on your upper back.
Grip the barbell slightly wider than shoulder-width, with your palms facing forward or slightly angled.
Keep your chest up, core braced, and a natural arch in your back as you initiate the squat by bending your hips and knees.
Lower your body by pushing your hips back and bending your knees until your thighs are parallel to the ground or lower.
Push through your heels to stand back up, extending your hips and knees.

title: Dumbbell Goblet Squat
steps: Hold a dumbbell vertically close to your chest, gripping the sides of the dumbbell head.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart.
Initiate the squat by bending your hips and knees, lowering your body while keeping your chest up and back straight.
As you stand back up from the squat, press the dumbbell overhead, extending your arms fully.
Lower the dumbbell back to your chest while simultaneously descending into another squat. Repeat the sequence for the desired number of reps, maintaining proper form.

title: Bulgarian Split Squat
steps: Stand a few feet away from a bench or platform.
Place one foot behind you on the bench, laces down.
Lower your back knee towards the ground, creating a 90-degree angle with both knees.
Keep your chest up and core engaged for stability.
Push through your feet to stand back up.

title: Kettlebell Step Up
steps: Stand in front of a platform or bench with a kettlebell in one hand.
Place one foot on the platform, ensuring your entire foot is firmly planted.
Push through the heel of the elevated foot to lift your body onto the platform.
Step down with control, returning to the starting position.
Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions on one leg, then switch to the other leg.

title: Kettlebell Goblet Squat
steps: Hold a kettlebell close to your chest with both hands, gripping the sides of the handle.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart or whatever feels comfortable.
Initiate the squat by bracing your core, bending your hips and knees, lowering your body while keeping your chest up and back straight.
Lower yourself until your thighs are parallel to the ground or lower.
Push through your feet to stand back up, extending your hips and knees.

title: Kettlebell Elevated Goblet Squat
steps:
Place 2 weight plates next to each other and stand with your heels on the plates and toes on the ground, heels shoulder-width apart or whatever feels comfortable.
Hold a kettlebell close to your chest with both hands, gripping the sides of the handle
Initiate the squat by bracing your core, bending your hips and knees, lowering your body while keeping your chest up and back straight.
Lower yourself until your thighs are parallel to the ground or lower.
Push through your feet to stand back up, extending your hips and knees.

title: Kettlebell Reverse Lunge
steps: Hold a kettlebell in front of your chest with both hands, gripping the sides of the handle.
Stand upright with your feet hip-width apart.
Step one foot backward and lower your back knee towards the ground, forming a 90-degree angle with both knees.
Push through your front heel to return to the starting position.
Alternate legs and repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, maintaining proper form throughout.
How to do a Kettle Bell Reverse Lunge in 5 points without highlights

title: Kettlebell Forward Lunge
steps: Hold a kettlebell in front of your chest with both hands, gripping the sides of the handle.
Stand upright with your feet hip-width apart.
Step one foot forward and lower your back knee towards the ground, forming a 90-degree angle with both knees.
Push through your front heel to return to the starting position.
Alternate legs and repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, maintaining proper form throughout.

title: Kettlebell Lateral Lunge
steps: Hold a kettlebell in front of your chest with both hands, gripping the sides of the handle.
Stand upright with your feet hip-width apart.
Step one foot out a wide distance to the side, bending the knee and pushing your hips back into a lunge position.
Push through foot to return to the starting position.
Alternate legs and repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, maintaining proper form throughout.

title: Side Lunges
steps: Stand upright with your feet hip-width apart.
Step one foot out a wide distance to the side, bending the knee and pushing your hips back into a lunge position.
Push through foot to return to the starting position.
Alternate legs and repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, maintaining proper form throughout.

title: Forward Lunges
steps: Stand upright with your feet hip-width apart.
Step one foot forward and lower your back knee towards the ground, forming a 90-degree angle with both knees.
Push through your front heel to return to the starting position.
Alternate legs and repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions, maintaining proper form throughout.

title: Jump Squats
steps: Begin by standing upright with your feet shoulder width apart, or your normal squat stance.
Brace your core and get into a squat.
Explosively jump upward from the squat, keeping your core braced.
Land softly back into the squat position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

title: Bodyweight Squat
steps: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned outward, and brace your core.
Lower your body by bending your hips and knees, pushing your hips back as if sitting in a chair.
Lower yourself until your thighs are parallel to the ground or as comfortable.
Push through your feet to stand back up, extending your hips and knees fully.

title: Barbell Curtsy Lunge
steps: Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a barbell across your upper back, brace your core.
Take a step diagonally back and behind your opposite leg, crossing your trailing leg behind your lead leg.
At the same time bend both knees, lowering your body towards the ground while keeping your chest up.
Ensure both knees are at 90-degree angles.
Push through your front foot to return to the starting position.
Repeat the movement on the alternate leg.

title: Spanish Squat
steps: Loop the resistance band around a sturdy anchor point and place each end behind each knee.
Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart, keep your core engaged.
Lower your body by bending your hips and knees, pushing your hips back.
Lower yourself until your thighs are parallel to the ground or as comfortable.
Push through your heels to stand back up, extending your hips and knees fully.

title: Resistance Band Leg Press
steps: Attach a resistance band securely to a fixed anchor point or hold the band near your head.
Lie on your back with your feet positioned against the band.
Bend one knee and place your foot flat on the band.
Straighten your legs against the resistance of the band.
Bend your knees again and bring your feet back to the starting position.

title: Resistance Band Squat
steps: Step on a resistance band with both feet, positioning it under the arches, feeling a tension in the band.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your core engaged.
Squat until your thighs are parallel to the ground or as comfortable.
Push through your feet and stand back up.

title: Dumbbell Goblet Bulgarian Split Squat
steps:
Hold a dumbbell close to your chest with both hands, gripping the sides of the dumbbell head.
Stand a few feet away from a bench or platform and place one foot behind you on the bench, laces down.
Lower your knees towards the ground, creating a 90-degree angle with both knees.
Push through your front heel to stand back up. 
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions on one leg, then switch to the other leg.

title: Barbell Bulgarian Split Squat
steps: Place a barbell across your upper back, gripping it with your hands slightly more than shoulder width.
Stand a few feet away from a bench or platform and place one foot behind you on the bench, laces down.
Lower your knees towards the ground, creating a 90-degree angle with both knees.
Push through your front foot to stand back up.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions on one leg, then switch to the other leg.

title: Barbell Front Squat Clean Grip
steps: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned outward.
Hold the barbell with a clean grip, placing your fingertips under the barbell and your elbows pointing forward.
Brace your core, and lift the barbell off the rack and position it on your upper chest and front shoulders.
Squat by bending your hips and knees.
Push through your feet to stand back up.

title: Barbell Front Squat Cross Grip
steps: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned outward.
Hold the barbell with a crossgrip, placing your fingers and thumb of one hand under the barbell and the other hand over the barbell.
Brace your core, and lift the barbell off the rack and position it on your upper chest and front shoulders.
Squat by bending your hips and knees.
Lower yourself until your thighs are parallel to the ground or as comfortable, then push through your heels to stand back up.

title: Barbell High Bar Squat
steps: Place the barbell on your upper traps, just below the base of your neck.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned outward.
Brace your core and squat until your thighs are below parallel or a depth that is comfortable for you.
Push through your feet to stand back up.

title: Barbell Low Bar Squat
steps: Place the barbell on your upper back, slightly lower than the High Bar position, resting on your rear deltoids.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned outward.
Brace your core and squat until your thighs are below parallel or a depth that is comfortable for you.
Push through your feet to stand back up.

title: Dumbbell Bulgarian Split Squat
steps: Hold a dumbbell in each hand by your sides.
Stand a few feet away from a bench or platform.
Place one foot behind you on the bench, laces down.
Push through your front heel to stand back up.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions on one leg, then switch to the other leg. Maintain proper form throughout the exercise.

title: Mid Stance Deadlift
steps: Assume a stance that's in between what you would use for a sumo deadlift and a regular deadlift.
Brace your core, hinge at the hips and grip the barbell with overhand grip, hands outside the hips.
Lift the barbell by extending hips and standing up.
Lower the barbell by hinging hips and bending knees.

title: Barbell Lunge
steps: Stand with your feet hip-width apart and hold a barbell on your upper back with both hands.
Brace your core and take a step forward with one leg lowering your body until both knees are bent at 90-degree angles.
Push through your front foot to return to the starting position.
Alternate legs and repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

title: Barbell Clean Grip Step Up
steps: Stand in front of a bench, platform, or sturdy box with a barbell placed on your upper chest and front shoulders using a clean grip.
Brace your core and place one foot on the bench.
Push through the heel of the elevated foot to lift your body onto the bench.
Step down with the leg you just raised returning to the starting position.
Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions on one leg, then switch to the other leg.

title: Barbell Heel Elevated Back Squat
steps: Place small weight plates under your heels to elevate them slightly.
Position the barbell across your upper back, gripping it with both hands.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned outward.
Engage your core, and squat down until your thighs are parallel to the ground or as comfortable.
Push through your feet to stand back up.

title: Barbell Heel Elevated Front Squat
steps:
Place small weight plates under your heels to elevate them slightly.
Position the barbell across your upper chest, and front shoulders with both your hands using a clean grip.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned outward.
Engage your core, and squat down until your thighs are parallel to the ground or as comfortable.
Push through your feet to stand back up.

title: Barbell Lateral Lunge
steps: Stand holding a barbell on your upper back with both hands and your feet shoulder-width apart.
Brace your core and take a wide step to the side, bending one knee and pushing your hips back.
Keep your other leg straight.
Push through the foot of the lunging leg to return to the starting position.
Alternate sides and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

title: Paused Barbell Box Squat
steps: Set up a box or bench behind you and position the barbell on your upper back.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned outward.
Squat until you lightly touch the box with your glutes.
Pause for a second while maintaining tension.
Push through your heels to stand back up.

title: Pause Squat with Barbell
steps: Set up a box or bench behind you and position the barbell on your upper back.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned outward.
Squat until you lightly touch the box with your glutes.
Pause for a second while maintaining tension.
Push through your heels to stand back up.

title: Reverse Deadlift
steps: Stand with your feet hip-width apart with a barbell right behind your legs.
Brace your core, hinge at the hips, bend your knees, and hold the barbell behind you using an overhand grip.
Keeping your core braced stand up dragging the barbell along the back of your leg.
Lower the barbell and return to the starting position

title: Barbell Reverse Lunge
steps: Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a barbell on your upper back with both hands.
Engage your core, take a step backward with one leg, bending both knees and lowering your body.
Lower yourself until your back knee is close to the ground and your front thigh is parallel to the ground.
Push through the front foot to return to the starting position.
Alternate legs and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

title: Reverse Step Up
steps: Place a bench, box, or platform behind you.
Engage your core and place the balls of one foot on the bench/box/platform behind you.
Push through balls of your elevated foot to lift your body and stand on the platform.
Return to the starting position.
Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions on one leg, then switch to the other leg.

title: Barbell Lateral Step Up
steps: Stand beside a bench, platform, or box with a barbell on your upper back.
Place one foot on the bench, ensuring your entire foot is firmly planted.
Push through the elevated foot to lift your body onto the bench.
Step down with control, returning to the starting position.
Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions on one leg, then switch to the other leg.

title: Barbell Split Squat
steps: Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a barbell on your upper back with both hands.
Step forward with one foot and a step backward with the other, creating a split stance.
Brace your core and lower your body by bending both knees.
Lower yourself until your back knee is close to the ground and your front thigh is parallel to the ground.
Push through the heel of the front foot to return to the starting position.
Alternate legs and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

title: Barbell Step Up With Kick
steps: Stand in front of a bench with a barbell across your back.
Place one foot on the bench, ensuring your entire foot is firmly planted.
Push through the heel of the elevated foot to lift your body onto the bench.
As your opposite foot comes up, kick it up to form a 90-degree angle with your hip.
Lower your opposite foot, returning to the starting position.
Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions on one leg, then switch to the other leg.

title: Barbell Step Up
steps: Stand in front of a bench or platform with a barbell on your upper back.
Place one foot on the bench, ensuring your entire foot is firmly planted.
Push through the heel of the elevated foot to lift your body onto the bench.
Step down with control, returning to the starting position.
Repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions on one leg, then switch to the other leg.

title: Barbell Touch Box Squat
steps: Set up a box or bench behind you and position the barbell on your upper back.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned outward.
Engage your core and squat until your glutes lightly touch the box.
Without pausing push through your heels to stand back up.

title: Barbell Zercher Squat
steps: Position the barbell in the crooks of your elbows, holding it close to your body, making a fist with your hands and pressing them together.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned outward.
Engage your core and squat until your thighs are parallel to the ground or as comfortable.
Push through your feet to stand back up.

title: Curtsy Lunge
steps: Stand with your feet hip-width apart, hands on your hips or in front of you for balance.
Take a step diagonally back and place one leg and behind your opposite leg, crossing your trailing leg behind your lead leg.
Bend both knees, lowering your body until your front thigh is parallel to the ground.
Push through your front foot to return to the starting position.
Alternate legs and repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

title: Lunge
steps: Stand with your feet hip-width apart, hands on your hips or at your sides.
Step forward with one leg, bending both knees and lowering your body.
Lower yourself until your front thigh is parallel to the ground and your back knee is close to the ground.
Push through the front foot to return to the starting position.
Alternate legs and repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

title: Elevated Heel Squat
steps: Stand with your feet hip-width apart with your heels slightly elevated on weight plates or platform.
Brace your core, and squat.
Lower yourself until your thighs are parallel to the ground or as comfortable.
Push through your feet to stand back up.

title: Lateral Lunge
steps: Stand with your feet hip-width apart, hands on your hips or at your sides.
Brace your core and take a wide step to the side with one leg, bending that knee and pushing your hips back.
Keep your other leg straight.
Push through the foot of the lunging leg to return to the starting position.
Alternate sides and repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

title: Reverse Lunge
steps: Stand with your feet hip-width apart, hands on your hips or at your sides.
Take a step backward with one leg, bending both knees and lowering your body.
Lower yourself until your back knee is close to the ground and your front thigh is parallel to the ground.
Push through the front foot to return to the starting position.
Alternate legs and repeat the movement for the desired number of reps.

title: Split Squat
steps: Stand with your feet hip-width apart, hands on your hips or at your sides.
Take a step forward with one leg and a step backward with the other, creating a split stance.
Brace your core and bend both knees.
Lower yourself until your back knee is close to the ground and your front thigh is parallel to the ground.
Push through the the front foot to return to the starting position.
Alternate legs and repeat the movement for the desired number of reps.

title: Dumbbell Lunge
steps: Hold a dumbbell in each hand by your sides using a neutral grip (palms facing each other).
Stand with your feet hip-width apart, hands on your hips or at your sides.
Brace your core and take a wide step forward with one leg, bending both knees and lowering your body.
Lower yourself until your front thigh is parallel to the ground and your back knee is close to the ground.
Push through the front foot to return to the starting position.
Alternate legs and repeat the movement for the desired number of reps.

title: Goblet Curtsy Lunge
steps: Hold a dumbbell close to your chest with both palms gripping the bottom of one head vertically.
Stand with your feet hip-width apart, and your core braced.
Take a step diagonally back and behind your opposite leg, crossing your trailing leg behind your lead leg.
Bend both knees, lowering your body until your front thigh is parallel to the ground.
Push through the front foot to return to the starting position.
Alternate legs and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

title: Goblet Forward Lunge
steps: Hold a dumbbell close to your chest with both palms gripping the bottom of one head vertically.
Stand with your feet hip-width apart, and your core braced.
Take a wide step forward with one leg, bending both knees and lowering your body until your front thigh is parallel to the ground.
Push through the front foot to return to the starting position.
Alternate legs and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

title: Goblet Lateral Lunge
steps: Hold a dumbbell close to your chest with both palms gripping the bottom of one head vertically.
Stand with your feet hip-width apart, and your core braced.
Take a wide step to the side with one leg, bending that knee and pushing your hips back.
Keep your other leg straight.
Push through the foot of the lunging leg to return to the starting position.
Alternate sides and repeat the movement for the desired number of reps.

title: Goblet Reverse Lunge
steps: Hold a dumbbell close to your chest with both palms gripping the bottom of one head vertically.
Stand with your feet hip-width apart, and your core braced.
Take a wide step backward with one leg, bending both knees and lowering your body until your back knee is close to the ground and your front thigh is parallel to the ground.
Push through the heel of the front foot to return to the starting position.
Alternate legs and repeat the movement for the desired number of reps.

title: Goblet Split Squat
steps: Hold a dumbbell close to your chest with both palms gripping the bottom of one head vertically.
Take a step forward with one leg and a step backward with the other, creating a split stance and your core braced.
Lower your body by bending both knees.
Lower yourself until your back knee is close to the ground and your front thigh is parallel to the ground.
Push through the front foot to return to the starting position.
Alternate legs and repeat the movement for the desired number of reps.

title: Dumbbell Lateral Lunge To Reach
steps: Hold a dumbbell in one hand by your side with an overhand grip.
Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding the dumbbell close to your body, and your core braced.
Take a wide step to the side with the leg opposite to the hand holding the dumbbell, bending that knee and pushing your hips back.
Keep your other leg straight and your chest up as you lower your body.
As you take a step, begin hinging at your hips and let the dumbbell reach down towards the foot of the lunging leg.
Pause for a moment at the lowest point you can comfortably lunge.
Push back through the foot of your active leg and straighten your chest to pull the dumbbell back up.
Repeat the movement for the desired number of reps and then switch to the opposite side.

title: Dumbbell Reverse Lunge
steps: Hold a dumbbell in each hand by your sides using a neutral grip (palms facing inwards).
Stand with your feet hip-width apart, hands holding the dumbbells close to your body.
Take a step backward with one leg, bending both knees and lowering your body until your back knee is close to the ground and your front thigh is parallel to the ground.
Push through the front foot to return to the starting position.
Alternate legs and repeat the movement for the desired number of reps.

title: Dumbbell Split Squat
steps: Hold a dumbbell in each hand by your sides using a neutral grip (palms facing inwards).
Holding the dumbbells close to your body take a step forward with one leg and a step backward with the other, creating a split stance.
Brace your core and lower your body by bending both knees.
Lower yourself until your back knee is close to the ground and your front thigh is parallel to the ground.
Push through the front foot to return to the starting position.
Alternate legs and repeat the movement for the desired number of reps.

title: Dumbbell  Paused Squat Front Rack
steps: Hold a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height, elbows pointed forward.
Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding the dumbbells close to your body and your core braced.
Squat down and pause for a few seconds at the bottom of the squat.
Push through your feet to stand back up.

title: Dumbbell Squat Front Rack
steps: Hold a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height, elbows pointed forward.
Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding the dumbbells close to your body and your core braced.
Squat down.
Push through your feet to stand back up.

title: Dumbbell Goblet Pulse Squat
steps: Hold a dumbbell close to your chest with both palms holding the bottom of one head vertically
Stand with your feet hip-width apart, hands holding the dumbbell close to your body and your core braced.
Squat down.
Once you're in the squat position, perform small, controlled pulses by moving up and down slightly.
After completing the pulses, push through your feet to stand back up. This is one rep.

title: Dumbbell Elevated Heel Goblet Squat
steps: Hold a dumbbell close to your chest with both palms holding the bottom of one head vertically
Place small weight plates or platforms under your heels to elevate them slightly.
Stand with your feet hip-width apart, hands holding the dumbbell close to your body and your core braced.
Squat down.
Push through your heels to stand back up.

title: Dumbbell Elevated Heels Narrow Goblet Squat
steps: Hold a dumbbell close to your chest with both palms holding the bottom of one head vertically
Place small weight plates or platforms under your heels to elevate them slightly.
Stand with your feet close together, hands holding the dumbbell close to your body and your core braced.
Squat down.
Push through your heels to stand back up.

title: Dumbbell Leg Extension
steps: Sit on a bench with your core braced.
Hold the dumbbell between your feet with your ankles flexed.
Extend your legs by lifting the dumbbell upward using your feet, contracting your quads.
Pause at the top of the movement, feeling the tension in your quads.
Lower the dumbbell back down slowly to the starting position.

title: Offset Dumbbell Squat
steps: Hold a dumbbell in one hand at shoulder height.
Stand with your feet hip-width apart.
Brace your core and squat down.
Push through your feet and stand back up.

title: Dumbbell Sumo Squat
steps: Hold a dumbbell with both hands in front of your body, gripping the bottom of one head vertically.
Let your arms fully extend down.
Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart, toes pointed slightly outward.
Brace your core and squat until your thighs are parallel to the ground or as comfortable.
Push through your feet to stand back up.

title: Dumbbell Thruster
steps: Hold a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height using a neutral grip (palms facing inward).
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart.
Brace your core and squat down.
As you stand back up, simultaneously press the dumbbells overhead, extending your arms fully.
Lower the dumbbells back to shoulder height.

title: Plate Squat
steps: Hold a weight with both hand using the sides of the plate at shoulder height.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart.
Brace your core and squat down.
Push through your feet to stand back up.

title: Plate Squat Reach
steps: Hold a weight with both hand using the sides of the plate at shoulder height close to your chest.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart.
Brace your core and squat down.
As you squat, simultaneously push the plate out.
Push through your feet to stand back up and simultaneously pulling the plate back to your chest.

title: Curtsy Lunge With Plate
steps: Hold a weight with both hand using the sides of the plate at shoulder height close to your chest.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart.
Take a step diagonally back and behind your opposite leg, crossing your trailing leg behind your lead leg.
Lower your body into a curtsy lunge by bending both knees.
Push through the front foot to return to the starting position.
Alternate legs and repeat the movement for the desired number of reps.

title: Plate Lateral Lunge
steps: Hold a weight plate by its sides around shoulder height in front of your chest.
Stand with your feet hip-width apart.
Take a wide step to the side with one leg, bending that knee and pushing your hips back.
Keep your other leg straight.
Push through the foot of the lunging leg to return to the starting position.
Alternate sides and repeat the movement for the desired number of reps.

title: Plate Lunge
steps: Hold a weight plate by its sides around shoulder height in front of your chest.
Stand with your feet hip-width apart.
Step forward with one leg, bending both knees and lowering your body.
Lunge until your front thigh is parallel to the ground and your back knee is close to the ground.
Push through the foot of the lunging leg to return to the starting position.
Alternate sides and repeat the movement for the desired number of reps.

title: Plate Reverse Lunge With Twist
steps: Hold a weight plate by its sides around shoulder height in front of your chest.
Stand with your feet hip-width apart.
Take a step backward with one leg, bending both knees and lowering your body.
Lower yourself until your back knee is close to the ground and your front thigh is parallel to the ground.
At the bottom of the lunge, twist your torso towards the side of the forward leg.
Return your torso to the forward position and push through the heel of the front foot to return to the starting position.
Alternate legs and repeat the movement for the desired number of reps.

title: Plate Reverse Lunge
steps: Hold a weight plate by its sides around shoulder height in front of your chest.
Stand with your feet hip-width apart.
Take a step backward with one leg, bending both knees and lowering your body.
Lower yourself until your back knee is close to the ground and your front thigh is parallel to the ground.
Push through the heel of the front foot to return to the starting position.
Alternate legs and repeat the movement for the desired number of reps.

title: Band Leg Extension
steps: Attach a resistance band to a stable anchor point, such as a sturdy pole or door anchor.
Place a bench in front of the anchor point.
Sit on the bench facing away from the anchor point with the band looped round your ankle.
Brace your core and extend your leg using your quads until your knees are straight.
Slowly return your leg to the starting position.

title: Plate Overhead Squat
steps: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart or slightly wider.
Hold a weight plate over your head with both hands by each side of the plate, arms fully extended.
Brace your core and squat while keeping the weight plate balanced overhead.
Lower yourself until your thighs are parallel to the ground or as comfortable.
Push through your feet to stand back up.

title: Deficit Lunge
steps: Stand with both feet on a plate and your core braced.
Step one foot backward on the ground and lower your back knee until it is close to the floor.
Push through your front foot and stand up bringing your rear foot to the starting position.
Alternate legs and repeat the movement for the desired number of reps.

title: Plate Overhead Walking Lunge
steps: Hold a weight plate over your head with both hands on either side of the plate, arms fully extended.
Brace your core, keep the weight plate balanced over your head and lunge forward with one leg.
Lower yourself until your thighs are parallel to the ground or as comfortable.
Push through the front foot to stand back up and bring your back foot forward to step into the next lunge.
Continue alternating legs and stepping forward.

title: Plate Squat Hold
steps: Hold a weight plate close to your chest with your hands gripping each side.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart or slightly wider.
Brace your core and get into a squat.
Hold the squat while holding the weight plate close to your chest.
Maintain the squat hold for your target duration.
Push through your feet and stand back up. This is one set.

title: Plate Thruster
steps: Hold a weight plate close to your chest with your hands gripping each side.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart or slightly wider.
Brace your core and get into a squat.
As you stand back up, use the momentum to press the weight plate overhead, extending your arms fully.
Lower the weight plate back to chest height and lower your body into the next squat.

title: Dumbbell Overhead Squat
steps: Hold a dumbbell in each hand overhead using a neutral grip (palms facing each other) and arms full extended.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart.
Brace your core and squat down.
As you squat keep the dumbbells balanced overhead and lower yourself as low as comfortable.
Push through your feet to stand back up.

title: Dumbbell Single Arm Overhead Squat
steps: Hold a dumbbell in one hand overhead using a neutral grip (palms facing towards your body), arm fully extended, while the other hand remains by your side.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart.
Brace your core and squat down.
As you squat keep the dumbbell balanced overhead and lower yourself as low as comfortable.
Push through your feet to stand back up.
Alternate the hand holding the dumbbell for each set.

title: Dumbbell Glute Bridge
steps: Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground, holding a dumbbell on your hips.
Brace your core, press through your feet and lift your hips off the ground, forming a straight line from your shoulders to your knees.
Squeeze your glutes at the top of the movement, ensuring your core is engaged.
Lower your hips back down.

title: Sumo Deadlift
steps: Stand behind a barbell with your feet in a very wide stance and your toes pointing slightly outward.
Hinge at your hips and knees to grip the barbell with a wide overhand grip, hands placed inside your legs.
Brace your core, lower your hips, and raise your chest.
Push through your feet and lift the barbell by extending your hips and knees simultaneously.
Stand upright ensuring your back stays neutral and shoulders are pulled back.
Lower the barbell back down to the ground by reversing the movement, keeping the barbell close to your body.

title: Plate Squat Hold To Reach
steps: Hold a weight plate close to your chest with both hands gripping each side.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart.
Brace your core and get into a squat and hold the lowered position.
While maintaining the squat, extend your arms forward, pushing the weight plat out and holding it for a moment.
Bring the weight plate back towards your chest.
Push through your feet and stand back up.

title: Single Leg Deadlift With Plate
steps: Hold a weight plate in front of your chest with both hands, gripping it horizontally.
Brace your core, and balance on one leg while keeping a slight bend in the knee.
Hinge at your hips and lower the weight plate towards the ground while extending your free leg behind you for balance.
Lower the weight plate as far as your flexibility allows while maintaining a flat back.
Push through the feet of your standing foot to return to the starting position.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions on one leg before switching to the other.

title: Dumbbell Seated Shrug
steps: Sit on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand, using a neutral grip(palms facing body).
Keep your arms fully extended, and your back straight.
Lift your shoulders towards your ears, squeezing your trapezius muscles.
Hold the contraction at the top for a brief moment.
Lower your shoulders back down to the starting position.

title: Kettlebell Shrug
steps: Hold a kettlebell in front of your hips with both your palms facing your body.
Stand with your feet hip-width apart and your core braced.
Lift your shoulders towards your ears, squeezing your trapezius muscles.
Hold the contraction at the top for a brief moment.
Lower your shoulders back down to the starting position.

title: Kettlebell Upright Row
steps: Hold a kettlebell in front of your hips with both your palms facing your body.
Stand upright with your feet hip-width apart and your core braced.
Lift the kettlebell towards your chin by raising your elbows out to the sides.
Keep the kettlebell close to your body as you lift it, focusing on your shoulder and upper back muscles.
Lower the kettlebell back down to the starting position.

title: Kettlebell Angled Shrug
steps: Hold a kettlebell in front of your hips with both your palms facing your body.
Stand upright with your feet hip-width apart and your core braced.
Hinge at your hips and bring your torso towards a 45-degree angle with a slight bend in your knees, letting your hands hang forward naturally.
Lift the kettlebell up by shrugging your shoulder blades together.
Lower the kettlebell back to the starting position holding the bend in your torso and knees.

title: Elevated Pike Shrug
steps: Place a bench/box behind you or stand with your back to an elevated surface.
Assume a push-up position with your toes on bench and palms on the group.
Walk your feet forward and lift your hips, forming an inverted V shape with your body.
Start by lowering your head toward the ground by squeezing your shoulder blades together and down.
Press back up towards the starting position. This is one rep.

title: Barbell Silverback Shrug
steps: Hold a barbell with both hands, palms facing your body, and grip slightly wider than shoulder-width.
Brace your core and stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent.
Hinge at your hips while keeping your back straight and chest up, similar to a bent-over row position.
Lift the barbell by shrugging your shoulders toward the ceiling, focusing on your trapezius muscles.
Hold the contraction at the top for a brief moment, then lower the barbell back down.

title: Band Shrug
steps: Stand on a resistance band with both feet, holding the ends of the band in each hand.
Keep your arms fully extended by your sides, palms facing your body, feeling a tension in your arms.
Lift your shoulders towards your ears, squeezing your trapezius muscles.
Hold the contraction at the top for a brief moment.
Lower your shoulders back down to the starting position.

title: Dumbbell Shrug
steps: Hold a dumbbell in each hand by your sides, palms facing your body.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your back straight.
Lift your shoulders towards your ears, focusing on your trapezius muscles.
Hold the contraction at the top for a brief moment.
Lower your shoulders back down to the starting position.

title: Barbell Shrug
steps: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell in front of you with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width.
Brace your core and keep your arms fully extended.
Lift your shoulders towards your ears, squeezing your trapezius muscles.
Hold the contraction at the top for a brief moment.
