Lower your shoulders back down to the starting position.

title: Side Lying Incline Shrug
steps: Set up an incline bench at a required angle (30 or 45 degrees).
Lie on your side letting your hand with the dumbbell hang down freely over the top of the bench.
Lift your shoulder towards your ear focusing on your trapezius muscles.
Hold the contraction at the top for a brief moment.
Lower your shoulder back down to the starting position.

title: Overhead Plate Carry
steps: Hold a weight plate overhead with both hands, arms fully extended.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart.
Engage your core and start walking forward, maintaining the plate overhead and your body stable.
Walking for a certain distance, time or steps.

title: Overhead Plate Shrug
steps: Hold a weight plate with both hands overhead, arms fully extended.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart.
Lift your shoulders towards your ears, focusing on your trapezius muscles.
Hold the contraction at the top for a brief moment.
Lower your shoulders back down to the starting position.

title: Kettlebell Incline Bench Shrug
steps: Set an incline bench to a comfortable angle and lie on it with your torso facing the backrest.
Hold a kettlebell with both hand, letting your arms hang down.
Lift your shoulders towards the ceiling, focusing on your trapezius muscles.
Hold the contraction at the top for a brief moment.
Lower your shoulders back down to the starting position.

title: Elevated Pike Press
steps: Set up an elevated surface, like a box or platform, behind you.
Get into a push-up position with your hands on the ground, your feet on the box and hips raised.
Walk your feet closer to your hands, raising your hips further and bringing your body into a pike position.
Start by bending your elbows to lower your head towards the ground.
Press through your palms to extend your arms and lift your head back up to the starting position.

title: Horizontal Shrug With Band
steps: Attach a resistance band to a stable anchor point at chest height.
Hold the resistance band with both hands, palms facing downward, and step back to create tension in the band and your arms extended forward.
Pull the resistance band horizontally towards your body by retracting your shoulder blades.
Hold the contraction for a brief moment, then release and allow the band to return to the starting position.

title: Band Single Arm Overhead Press
steps: Stand with one foot on one end of a resistance band.
Hold the other end in your hand at shoulder level with your elbow flexed feeling a tension in the band.
Press your hand upward while extending your elbow fully, pushing against the resistance of the band.
Hold the extended position briefly, then lower your hand back to shoulder height.
Repeat for the desired number of reps on each arm.

title: Barbell Upright Row
steps: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly narrower than shoulder-width.
Allow the barbell to hang in front of your hips, arms fully extended.
Brace your core and lift the barbell towards your chin by raising your elbows out to the sides.
Keep the barbell close to your body as you lift it, focusing on your shoulder and upper back muscles.
Lower the barbell back down to the starting position.

title: Barbell Z Press
steps: Sit on the floor with your core braced, your legs extended and straight in front of you.
Hold a barbell with a pronated grip (palms facing forward) at shoulder height.
Press the barbell above your head, locking out your elbows.
Lower the barbell down to the starting position.

title: Dumbbell Incline Bench Leaning Shrug
steps: Lie facedown on an incline bench.
Hold a dumbbell in each hand using a neutral grip (palms facing each other).
Let your arms hang down fully extended.
Shrug your shoulder towards the ceiling, focusing on your trapezius muscles.
Hold the contraction at the top for a brief moment.
Lower your shoulders back down to the starting position.

title: Dumbbell Leaning Shrug
steps: Hold a dumbbell in each hand using a neutral grip (palms facing each other).
Stand with your feet at shoulder-width, brace your core and bend your knees slightly.
Hinge at your hips to about 45 degrees, and your arms hang straight down.
Shrug your shoulder towards the ceiling, focusing on your trapezius muscles.
Hold the contraction at the top for a brief moment.
Lower your shoulders back down to the starting position.

title: Tricep Dips
steps: Place two boxes, or platforms either side of you.
Brace your core, place your palms on the box and extend your arms to lift yourself off the ground.
Bend your elbows to lower your body, keeping your body as upright as possible - this will bias the triceps.
Push through your palms to extend your arms and lift your body back up to the starting position.

title: Dumbbell Seated Overhead Tricep Extension
steps: Sit on a bench holding a dumbbell with both hands overhead, arms fully extended.
Keep your upper arms close to your head, and your elbows pointed forward.
Lower the dumbbell behind your head by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary.
Lower the dumbbell until your forearms are parallel to the ground or slightly below.
Extend your elbows to raise the dumbbell back to the starting position.

title: Bench Dips
steps: Position yourself with your back to a sturdy bench or chair.
Place your palms on the edge of the bench, fingers pointing forward.
Walk your feet forward, extending your legs and supporting your body weight on your hands.
Bend your elbows to lower your body, keeping your back close to the bench.
Lower yourself until your elbows are at a 90-degree angle or as comfortable.
Push through your palms to extend your arms and lift your body back up to the starting position.

title: Barbell Skull Crusher
steps: Lie on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and hold a barbell with an overhand grip at shoulder-width.
Extend your arms fully and hold the barbell above your chest.
Lower the barbell until your forearms are close to your head or as comfortable, feeling a stretch in your triceps.
Push through your palms to extend your arms and lift the barbell back to the starting position.

title: Kettlebell Skull Crusher
steps: Lie on your back with knees in the air and soles of your feet flat on the floor.
Hold the kettlebell in both hands directly above your chest.
Keeping your upper arms in place, bend your elbows to slowly bring the kettlebell in front of your forehead.
Return to the starting position and repeat.

title: Kettlebell Standing Tricep Extension
steps: Stand upright with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell with both hands.
Raise the kettlebell overhead with your arms fully extended.
Keeping your upper arms close to your head, bend your elbows to lower the kettlebell behind your head.
Lower the kettlebell until your forearms are parallel to the ground or slightly below, feeling a stretch in your triceps.
Extend your elbows to raise the kettlebell back to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of repetitions while maintaining proper form and control throughout.

title: Kettlebell Decline Skull Crusher
steps: Lie on an incline bench with your head lower than your hips and your feet flat on the ground and hold a kettlebell with both hands.
Extend your arms fully and hold the kettlebell above your chest.
Keeping your upper arms stationary, bend your elbows to lower the kettlebell towards your forehead.
Lower the kettlebell until your forearms are close to your head or as comfortable, feeling a stretch in your triceps.
Push through your palms to extend your arms and lift the kettlebell back to the starting position.

title: Kettlebell Tate Press
steps: Lie on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and hold a kettlebell by its handle  in one hand hand using a neutral grip (palm facing in).
Extend your loaded arm fully and hold the kettlebell above your chest.
Bend your elbow to lower the kettlebell towards your chest, keeping your upper arms perpendicular to the ground.
Lower the kettlebell until it is just above your chest, feeling a stretch in your triceps.
Reverse the move and lift the kettlebell back to the starting position.
After finishing the required number of reps on one hand, switch hands and do the exercise.

title: Diamond Push Ups
steps: Get into a push up position.
Move your hands close together and rotate them inwards forming a diamond shape with your thumbs and index fingers.
Do a push up.

title: Barbell Close Grip Bench Press
steps: Lie on a bench and hold the barbell with your hands positioned closer than shoulder-width apart.
Unrack the barbell and hold it above your chest, arms fully extended.
Lower the barbell towards your lower chest, keeping your elbows close to your body.
Touch your chest lightly with the barbell, then push it back up to the starting position.

title: Band Overhead Tricep Extension
steps: Attach a resistance band to a sturdy anchor close to the ground behind you or stand on the resistance band.
Pull the resistance band from behind up and it with both hands behind your head.
Hold your upper arms up vertically so your elbows face the ceiling.
Without moving your upper arms, pull the resistance band up by extending your elbows.
Extend your arms fully overhead, keeping your upper arms close to your head.
Bend your elbows to lower your hands behind your head, feeling a stretch in your triceps.

title: Band Pushdown
steps: Attach a resistance band to a high anchor point, such as a pull-up bar or sturdy hook.
Hold the other end of the resistance band with both hands, with your palms facing down.
Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your core braced.
Start with your elbows bent and at your chest.
Push down on the resistance band, extending your elbows fully, and feel the contraction in your triceps.
Return to the starting position by bending your elbows.

title: Band Skullcrusher
steps: Attach a resistance band to a sturdy anchor point.
Lie on a flat bench so that the anchor point is above the top of your head.
Hold the other end of the resistance band with both hands, palms forward, arms fully extended overhead.
Bend your elbows to lower your hands towards your forehead, feeling a stretch in your triceps.
Extend your elbows to raise your hands back to the starting position.

title: Dumbbell Skullcrusher
steps: Lie on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and hold a dumbbell in each hand, arms extended above your chest using a neutral grip (hands facing each other).
Bend your elbows to lower the dumbbells towards your forehead, keeping your upper arms stationary.
Lower the dumbbells until your forearms are parallel to the ground or slightly below, feeling a stretch in your triceps.
Extend your elbows to raise the dumbbells back to the starting position.

title: Barbell Skullcrusher
steps: Lie on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and hold a barbell at shoulder width using an overhand grip (palms facing down).
Bend your elbows to lower the barbell towards your forehead, keeping your upper arms stationary.
Lower the barbell until your forearms are parallel to the ground or slightly below, feeling a stretch in your triceps.
Extend your elbows to raise the dumbbells back to the starting position.

title: Barbell Overhead Tricep Extension
steps: Stand upright and hold a barbell with an overhand grip, hands positioned slightly narrower than shoulder-width.
Raise and hold the barbell overhead, fully extending your arms.
Bend your elbows to lower the barbell behind your head and keep your upper arm stationary or close to your head as possible.
Lower the barbell until your forearms are parallel to the ground or slightly below, feeling a stretch in your triceps.
Extend your elbows to raise the barbell back to the starting position.

title: Dumbbell Decline Skullcrusher
steps: Lie down on an incline bench with your head lower than your hips, holding a dumbbell in each hand.
Extend your arms fully above your chest, palms facing each other.
Lower the dumbbells until your forearms are parallel to the ground or slightly below, feeling a stretch in your triceps.
Extend your elbows to raise the dumbbells back to the starting position.

title: Rolling Tricep Extension
steps: Start by lying on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand, arms fully extended above your chest, palms facing each other.
Bend your elbows to lower the dumbbells towards your forehead, keeping your upper arms stationary.
Lower the dumbbells until your forearms are parallel to the ground or slightly below, feeling a stretch in your triceps.
Rotate your shoulder bringing your upper arms back until they are parallel to the floor.
Pull your shoulders back, bringing the upper arms to the starting position and extending the elbows to bring the dumbbells back to the starting position.

title: Dumbbell Overhead Tricep Extension
steps: Stand upright and hold a dumbbell with both hands by the bottom of one head, palms facing upward, and arms extended overhead.
Keep your upper arms close to your head as you bend your elbows, lowering the dumbbell behind your head.
Lower the dumbbell until your forearms are parallel to the ground or slightly below, feeling a stretch in your triceps.
Extend your elbows to raise the dumbbell back to the starting position.

title: Dumbbell Tricep Kickback
steps: Start by holding a dumbbell in your right hand and placing your left knee and left hand on a bench for support.
Keep your right upper arm parallel to the ground, bending your right elbow to a 90-degree angle.
Extend your right elbow, straightening your arm fully, and kick the dumbbell back behind you.
Keep your upper arm stationary throughout the movement, feeling the contraction in your right tricep.
Lower the dumbbell back to the bent elbow position and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

title: Plate Overhead Tricep Extension
steps: Stand upright and hold a weight plate with both hands on either side, your arms fully extended above your head.
Keep your upper arms close to your head as you bend your elbows, lowering the weight plate behind your head.
Lower the weight plate until your forearms are parallel to the ground or slightly below, feeling a stretch in your triceps.
Extend your elbows to raise the weight plate back to the starting position.

title: Band Rapunzel Pushdown
steps: Attach a resistance band to a sturdy anchor point above your head.
Hold the other end of the resistance band with both hands, palms facing each other.
Stand with your back to the anchor point and extend your arms fully to create tension in the band.
Bend your elbows and bring your hands behind your head, keeping your upper arms close to your ears.
Push the band downward, extending your elbows fully, and feel the contraction in your triceps. Return to the starting position by bending your elbows.

title: Plate Overhead Press To Tricep Extension
steps: Hold a weight plate with both hands in front of your chest.
Perform an overhead press by pushing the weight plate upward above your head until your arms are fully extended.
Keep your upper arms close to your head as you bend your elbows, lowering the weight plate behind your head.
Lower the weight plate until your forearms are parallel to the ground or slightly below, feeling a stretch in your triceps.
Extend your elbows to raise the weight plate back overhead and lower the plate back to your chest to the starting position.

title: Band Single Arm Pushdown
steps: Attach a resistance band to a sturdy anchor point at shoulder height.
Stand facing the anchor point and hold the band's handle with one hand, palm facing down.
Position your elbow close to your side, your elbow bent and your forearm up.
Push the band downward by extending your elbow fully, feeling the contraction in your triceps.
Return to the starting position by bending your elbow.

title: Single Arm Rapunzel Pushdown
steps: Attach a resistance band to a sturdy anchor point above your head and behind you.
Hold the band's handle with one hand, palm facing down.
Step away from the anchor point to create tension in the band and position yourself at an angle.
Bend your elbow and bring your hand behind your head, keeping your upper arm close to your ear.
Push the band downward by extending your elbow fully, feeling the contraction in your triceps. Return to the starting position by bending your elbow.

title: Band Single Arm Skullcrusher
steps: Lie on a bench and attach a resistance band to a sturdy anchor point above the top of your head.
Hold the band's handle with one hand using a neutral grip (palm facing your body) and extend your arm forward in line with your chest.
Bend your elbow and bring your hand behind your head, keeping your upper arm stationary.
Extend your elbow to push the band down, feeling the contraction in your triceps.
Return to the starting position by bending your elbow.

title: Dumbbell Single Arm Overhead Tricep Extension
steps: Stand upright holding a dumbbell in one hand and raise it overhead.
Keep your upper arm close to your head as you bend your elbow, lowering the dumbbell behind your head.
Lower the dumbbell until your forearm is parallel to the ground or slightly below, feeling a stretch in your triceps.
Extend your elbow to raise the dumbbell back to the starting position.

title: Dumbbell Tate Press
steps: Lie down on a bench and hold a dumbbell in each hand using an overhand grip (palms facing down).
Start with the dumbbells positioned over your chest, arms fully extended.
Bend your elbows and flair your upper arms out lowering the dumbbells towards your chest.
Lower the dumbbells until they touch your chest.
Press the dumbbells back up to the starting position, extending your elbows and bringing your upper arms in.

title: Dumbbell Neutral Grip Seated Overhead Press
steps: Sit on a bench with back support, holding a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height, palms facing each other.
Press the dumbbells upward, extending your arms fully overhead while keeping your palms facing each other.
Lower the dumbbells back to shoulder height in a controlled manner.

title: Dumbbell Seated Arnold Press
steps: Sit on a bench with back support.
Hold a dumbbell in each hand facing your shoulders and your elbows bent, creating a 90-degree angle.
Press the dumbbells upward while simultaneously rotating your wrists, so your palms face forward at the top of the movement.
Reverse the motion by rotating your wrists back to the starting position and lowering the dumbbells to shoulder height.

title: Dumbbell Alternating Arnold Press
steps: Stand upright with your core braced.
Hold a dumbbell in each hand facing your shoulders and your elbows bent, creating a 90-degree angle.
Press the dumbbell in one hand upward while simultaneously rotating your wrist, so your palm face forward at the top of the movement.
Do not move the other hand.
Reverse the motion by rotating your wrist back to the starting position and lowering the dumbbell to shoulder height.
Repeat the exercise on the opposite hand.

title: Dumbbell Alternating Overhead Press
steps: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your core braced.
Hold a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height, palms facing forward.
Press one dumbbell upward until your arm is fully extended overhead while keeping the other dumbbell at shoulder height.
Lower the pressed dumbbell back to shoulder height.
Press the other dumbbell overhead.
Continue alternating the pressing motion between the two arms.

title: Dumbbell Neutral Grip Alternating Overhead Press
steps: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your core braced.
Hold a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height using a neutral grip (palms facing each other).
Press one dumbbell upward until your arm is fully extended overhead while maintaining a neutral grip keeping the other dumbbell at shoulder height.
Lower the pressed dumbbell back to shoulder height.
Press the other dumbbell overhead.
Continue alternating the pressing motion between the two arms.

title: Dumbbell Neutral Overhead Press
steps: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your core braced.
Hold a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height using a neutral grip (palms facing each other).
Press both dumbbells upward until your arms are fully extended overhead while maintaining a neutral grip.
Lower the dumbbells back to shoulder height.

title: Dumbbell Overhead Press
steps: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your core braced.
Hold a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height using an overhand grip (palms facing forward).
Press both dumbbells upward until your arms are fully extended overhead.
Lower the dumbbells back to shoulder height.

title: Dumbbell Push Press
steps: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height, palms facing each other.
Brace your core, bend your knees slightly and dip your hips.
Explosively push through your legs and use the momentum to assist in pressing the dumbbells overhead.
Fully extend your arms at the top of the movement while keeping your core engaged.
Lower the dumbbells back to shoulder height in a controlled manner.
Repeat for the desired number of reps.

title: Dumbbell Single Arm Arnold Press
steps: Stand upright with your feet shoulder width apart.
Start with your palm facing you at shoulder level and your elbow bent, creating a 90-degree angle.
Press the dumbbell upward while simultaneously rotating your wrist, so your palm faces forward at the top of the movement.
Extend your arm fully overhead.
Reverse the motion by rotating your wrist back to the starting position and lowering the dumbbell to shoulder height.
Repeat for the desired number of reps.
Switch to the other arm and repeat the process.

title: Dumbbell Single Arm Neutral Overhead Press
steps: Stand upright with your feet shoulder width apart.
Hold a dumbbell in one hand at shoulder height, using a neutral grip (palm facing inward) and elbow bent.
Press the dumbbell upward, extending your arm fully overhead while maintaining the neutral grip.
Lower the dumbbell back to shoulder height in a controlled manner.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions on one arm, then switch to the other arm.

title: Dumbbell Single Arm Overhead Press
steps: Stand upright with your feet shoulder width apart.
Hold a dumbbell in one hand at shoulder height, palm facing forward.
Press the dumbbell upward, extending your arm fully overhead.
Lower the dumbbell back to shoulder height in a controlled manner.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions on one arm, then switch to the other arm.

title: Dumbbell Lateral Raise
steps: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand by your sides, palms facing your body.
Keep a slight bend in your elbows and brace your core.
Lift both dumbbells out to the sides, maintaining a slight bend in your elbows, until your arms are parallel to the ground.
Pause briefly at the top of the movement, feeling the contraction in your lateral deltoids.
Lower the dumbbells back down to your sides in a controlled manner.

title: Dumbbell Rear Delt Fly
steps: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand by your sides, palms facing each other.
Brace your core, bend your hips slightly forward and maintain a slight bend in your elbows.
Lift both dumbbells out to the sides while keeping your arms straight, focusing on squeezing your rear deltoids.
Lift your arms until they are parallel to the ground or slightly higher.
Lower the dumbbells back down in a controlled manner.

title: Dumbbell Seated Overhead Press
steps: Sit on a bench with back support, holding a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height, palms facing forward.
Press the dumbbells upward, extending your arms fully overhead.
Lower the dumbbells back to shoulder height.

title: Dumbbell Front Raise
steps: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart.
Hold s dumbbell in each hand by your sides, using an overhand grip (palms facing your body).
Lift both dumbbells straight in front of you, keeping your arm extended until it reaches shoulder height.
Lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position.

title: Dumbbell Seated Rear Delt Fly
steps: Sit on a bench with back support, holding a dumbbell in each hand by your sides using a neutral grip (palms facing each other).
Keep a slight bend in your elbows and brace your core and lean slightly forward from your hips.
Lift both dumbbells out to the sides, focusing on squeezing your rear deltoids.
Lift your arms until they are parallel to the ground or slightly higher, then lower the dumbbells back down in a controlled manner.

title: Kettlebell Rear Delt Row
steps: Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a kettlebell in eact hand with an overhand grip (palm facing your body).
Brace your core and bend your hips at a 45 degree angle.
Let the kettlebells hang directly below your shoulders
Row the kettlebells towards your chest by pulling back with your shoulder blades and   flaring your elbows.
Focus on squeezing your rear deltoid muscles at the top of the movement.
Lower the kettlebell back down in a controlled manner.

title: Kettlebell Front Raise
steps: Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a kettlebell with both hands using an overhand grip (palm facing down).
Brace your core.
Lift the kettlebell straight in front of you keeping your arms extended fully.
Raise your arm until it reaches shoulder height.
Lower the kettlebell back down to the starting position.

title: Kettlebell Single Arm Rear Delt Fly
steps: Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a kettlebell in one hand with a neutral grip (palm facing your body).
Bend at the hips while keeping your back straight, and let the kettlebell hang directly below your shoulder.
Lift the kettlebell out to the side in a wide arc retracting your shoulder blade and keeping your elbow slightly bent.
Focus on squeezing your rear deltoid muscles at the top of the movement.
Lower the kettlebell back down in a controlled manner.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions on one side, then switch to the other side.

title: Kettlebell Lever Laterals
steps: Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a kettlebell in one hand with an overhand grip (palm facing down).
Engage your core and keep your arm straight.
Lift the kettlebell out to the side, maintaining a controlled and steady motion.
Grip the kettlebell tightly do it keeps its orientation.
Lower the kettlebell back down in a controlled manner.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions on one side, then switch to the other side.

title: Kettlebell Single Arm Lateral Raise
steps: Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a kettlebell in one hand with a neutral grip (palm facing your body).
Keep a slight bend in your elbow.
Lift the kettlebell out to the side.
Raise your arm until it reaches shoulder height, keeping the slight bend in your elbow.
Lower the kettlebell back down.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions on one side, then switch to the other side.

title: Band Face Pull
steps: Attach a resistance band to a sturdy anchor at eye level.
Hold the ends of the band in each hand with an neutral grip (palms facing each other).
Step back to create tension in the band, and stand with your feet shoulder-width apart.
Pull the band towards your face by retracting your shoulder blades and squeezing your upper back muscles.
Break at your elbows and bring your hands to the sides of your face, keeping your elbows elevated.
Hold for a moment, then release back to the starting position.

title: Band Front Raise
steps: Attach a resistance band to a sturdy anchor at floor level or place both your feet on top of it.
Hold the other end of the band with both hands using an overhand grip (palm facing down).
Stand with your feet hip-width apart.
Lift the banded hand straight in front of you keeping your arms extended.
Raise your arm until it reaches shoulder height.
Lower the band back down.

title: Band Lateral Raise
steps: Place both your feet on top of a resistance band.
Hold one end of the band in each hand with and overhand grip.
Lift the banded hand out to both sides.
Raise your arm until it reaches shoulder height keeping it extended.
Lower the band back down.

title: Band Pull Apart
steps: Hold a resistance band with both hands, gripping it slightly wider than shoulder-width apart.
Begin with the band at chest level, pulling it apart by moving your hands outwards while engaging your shoulder blades.
Continue pulling the band until your hands are positioned at shoulder level or slightly above.
Slowly return your hands to the starting position with control, allowing the band to come back together.

title: Barbell Front Raise
steps: Stand up straight with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell with an overhand grip (palms facing down).
Keep your arms extended in front of you, holding the barbell at thigh level.
Brace your core and lift the barbell straight up in front of you keeping your arm completely extended.
Lift until your arms are parallel to the floor or slightly higher.
Pause briefly at the top of the movement, engaging your front shoulder muscles.
Slowly lower the barbell back down to the starting position.

title: Barbell Overhead Press
steps: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and the barbell racked at shoulder level.
Grip the barbell slightly wider than shoulder-width, palms facing forward. Your wrists should be aligned with your forearms.
Brace your core and engage your glutes. Press the barbell overhead by extending your arms fully while exhaling.
Keep your head neutral and avoid leaning back excessively. The barbell should move in a straight line.
Once the barbell is overhead, pause briefly and then lower it back down to shoulder level while inhaling.

title: Dumbbell Rear Delt Row
steps:
Hold a dumbbell in each hand and stand with your feet shoulder-width apart.
Bend at your hips while maintaining a flat back and a slight bend in your knees. Let the dumbbells hang in front of you with an overhand grip.
Keep your elbows slightly bent and lift the dumbbells out wide to the sides, leading with your elbows. Focus on squeezing your rear deltoid muscles as you lift.
Raise the dumbbells until your upper arms are parallel to the ground or slightly higher.
Lower the dumbbells back down with control to the starting position, maintaining proper form.

title: Dumbbell Bayesian Lateral Raise
steps: Lie facedown on an incline bench.
Hold a dumbbell in each hand and let your arms hang straight down.
Keep your elbows straight and lift the dumbbells out to the sides.
Raise the dumbbells until your upper arms are parallel to the ground or slightly higher.
Lower the dumbbells back down with control to the starting position.

title: Dumbbell Incline Bench Reverse Fly
steps: Set an incline bench at a 30-45 degree angle and lie face down on it, holding a dumbbell in each hand.
Allow your arms to hang down towards the floor with a slight bend in your elbows and your palms facing each other.
Engage your back muscles and raise the dumbbells wide out to the sides, leading with your elbows. Keep your arms in line with your shoulders.
Lift the dumbbells until your arms are parallel to the ground or slightly higher, feeling the squeeze in your rear deltoids.
Slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position with control.

title: Dumbbell Pronated Incline Bench Reverse Fly
steps: Set an incline bench at a 30-45 degree angle and lie face down on it, holding a dumbbell in each hand using a pronated grip (palms facing down).
Allow your arms to hang down towards the floor with a slight bend in your elbows and your palms facing each other.
Engage your back muscles and raise the dumbbells wide out to the sides, leading with your elbows. Keep your arms in line with your shoulders.
Lift the dumbbells until your arms are parallel to the ground or slightly higher, feeling the squeeze in your rear deltoids.
Slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position with control.

title: Dumbbell Arnold Press
steps: Stand upright with your feet at shoulder width.
Hold a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height, palms facing your body, and your elbows bent.
Start with your palms facing your body. As you press the dumbbells overhead, simultaneously rotate your wrists so that your palms face forward at the top of the movement.
Press the dumbbells upward until your arms are fully extended overhead.
Reverse the motion by rotating your wrists back to the starting position as you lower the dumbbells back down to shoulder height.

title: Car Driver
steps: Stand upright and hold a weight plate with both hands, gripping it at the sides.
Hold the weight plate at chest height, away from your body, with your arms fully extended.
Begin the movement by rotating your wrists in a circular motion, as if you are steering a car's steering wheel.
Rotate the plate back to the starting position.
Continue the circular motion for the desired number of repetitions, and then switch directions to complete the set.
Maintain controlled movements and focus on using your core and shoulder muscles to guide the plate.

title: Plate Front Raise
steps: Stand upright and hold a weight plate with both hands, gripping it at the sides.
Keep your arms extended in front of you, holding the weight plate at waist level, with a slight bend in your elbows.
Raise the weight plate directly in front of you until it reaches shoulder height.
Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, feeling the contraction in your front shoulder muscles.
Slowly lower the weight plate back down to the starting position.

title: Plate Halo
steps: Hold a weight plate with both hands, gripping it at the sides, and stand with your feet shoulder-width apart.
Start by holding the weight plate close to your chest, with your elbows bent.
Begin the movement by lifting the weight plate up and over your head in a circular motion. Imagine drawing a halo around your head.
Continue the circular motion until the weight plate returns to the starting position in front of your chest.
Perform the desired number of repetitions in one direction and then switch to the opposite direction for the next set.

title: Band High Face Pull
steps: Attach a resistance band to a secure anchor point high above your head.
Stand facing the anchor point and hold the ends of the resistance band in each hand, palms facing each other.
Take a step or two back to create tension in the band.
Start with your arms fully extended in front of you, at shoulder height, and your elbows slightly bent.
Engage your shoulder blades and upper back muscles to pull the band towards your face. Keep your elbows high, aiming to bring them above shoulder level.
As you pull the band, focus on squeezing your shoulder blades together and contracting your rear deltoids.
Slowly release the tension and return to the starting position with controlled movement.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, focusing on proper form and controlled motions.

title: Band Low Anchor Lateral Raise
steps: Attach a resistance band to a secure anchor point at ankle level or lower.
Stand facing the anchor point and hold the ends of the resistance band in the hand opposite to the anchor.
Stand with the anchor to your side.
Engage your side deltoids (shoulder muscles) as you lift your arms outward and upward.
Lift your arms to shoulder level or slightly below, focusing on the contraction in your side deltoids.
Slowly lower your arms back to the starting position with controlled movement.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, focusing on maintaining proper form and controlled motions.

title: Band Mid Lateral Raise
steps: Attach a resistance band to a secure anchor point at waist level.
Stand facing the anchor point and hold the ends of the resistance band in the hand opposite to the anchor.
Stand with the anchor to your side.
Engage your side deltoids (shoulder muscles) as you lift your arms outward and upward.
Lift your arms to shoulder level or slightly below, focusing on the contraction in your side deltoids.
Slowly lower your arms back to the starting position with controlled movement.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, focusing on maintaining proper form and controlled motions.

title: Band Overhead Press
steps: Stand on resistance band or secure it to a low anchor point behind you.
Stand facing away from the anchor point and hold the ends of the resistance band in each hand, palms facing forward.
Position your feet shoulder-width apart and maintain a stable stance.
Start with your hands at shoulder level, elbows bent at 90 degrees.
Press your hands upward, extending your arms fully.
Lower your hands back to the starting position.

title: Band Rear Delt Fly
steps: Start by standing between the two anchored bands with your feet shoulder-width apart and the bands positioned at a high point.
Stand facing the anchor point and hold the ends of the resistance band in each hand, palms facing each other.
Take a step or two back to create tension in the band.
Begin with your arms extended in front of you, your elbows should have a slight bend.
Engage your rear deltoid muscles (muscles at the back of your shoulders) as you pull your arms outward and backwards squeezing your shoulder blades together.
Slowly let your arms go back towards the starting position.

title: Plate Full Overhead Lateral Raise
steps: Stand upright with your core braced.
Hold a weight plate in each hand with an overhand grip.
Lift both plates wide to the side as though you are doing a lateral raise.
Continue to raise the plates above your head until they touch each other.
As you raise the plates, rotate your hands so your palms face forward.
Reverse the movement back to the starting position

title: Plate Pronated Rear Delt Fly
steps: Stand upright with your core braced.
Hold a weight plate in each hand by its sides.
Brace your core and hinge at your hips until your torso is parallel to the ground.
Let both your hands hang forward.
Keep a slight bend in your elbows and lift the weight plate away from your body, focusing on using your rear deltoid muscles (muscles at the back of your shoulders).
As you lift, squeeze your shoulder blades together and lift the weight plate to shoulder level.
Slowly lower the weight plate back to the starting position with controlled movement.

title: Plate Lateral Raise
steps: Stand upright with your core braced.
Hold a weight plate in each hand by its sides in a neutral grip (palms facing your body).
Let both your hands hang by your sides with a slight bend in the elbows.
Lift the weight plate away from your body to the side, focusing on using your deltoid muscles.
Slowly lower the weight plate back to the starting position with controlled movement.

title: Plate Reverse Fly
steps: Stand upright with your core braced.
Hold a weight plate in each hand by its sides with a neutral grip(palms facing each other).
Brace your core and hinge at your hips until your torso is parallel to the ground.
Let both your hands hang forward.
Keep a slight bend in your elbows and lift the weight plate away from your body, focusing on using your rear deltoid muscles (muscles at the back of your shoulders).
As you lift, squeeze your shoulder blades together and lift the weight plate to shoulder level.
Slowly lower the weight plate back to the starting position with controlled movement.
As you raise the plates, rotate your hands so your palms face forward.
Reverse the movement back to the starting position

title: Standing Plate Reach
steps: Hold a weight plate with both hands at its sides, gripping it firmly.
Stand with feet shoulder-width apart and knees slightly bent.
Extend your arms in front of you, holding the plate at chest level.
Pull your arms back to your chest.

title: Side Lying  Lateral Raise
steps: Lie on your side on a flat bench.
Hold a dumbbell in your outer hand with a neutral grip with your arm along your side.
Engage your core and lift the dumbbells out to your sides while keeping a slight bend in your elbows.
Lift your arms until they are at your shoulder.
Lower the dumbbell back down.

title: Dumbbell Single Arm Upright Row
steps: Stand with your feet hip-width apart.
Hold a dumbbell in one hand with an overhand grip and your arm extended down.
Lift the dumbbell straight up toward your head along your body by raising your shoulder and breaking your elbow.
Continue to lift the weight until it reaches the chin or neck level, keeping the elbow high and close to the body.
Pause briefly at the top of the movement.
Lower back to the starting position.

title: Dumbbell Upright Row
steps: Stand with your feet hip-width apart.
Hold a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip and your arm extended down.
Lift the dumbbell straight up toward your head along your body by raising your shoulder and breaking your elbow.
Pause briefly at the top of the movement.
Lower back to the starting position.

title: Plate Clean And Press
steps: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a weight plate with both hands in front of your hips.
Lower into a squat position, keeping your back straight and the weight plate close to your body.
Explosively stand up while using your momentum to lift the weight plate to shoulder level, flipping it over so that the center hole faces upward.
Press the weight plate overhead by fully extending your arms, engaging your shoulders and core.
Lower the weight plate back to shoulder level and then return it to the starting position by reversing the clean motion.

title: Kettlebell Bent Over Shoulder Extensions
steps: Return to the starting position and repeat.

title: Band Row
steps: Stand on your band with both feet.
Hinge forward at the hips while keeping a flat back.
Let your arms hang freely, then pull your elbows straight back toward the ceiling.

title: Dumbbell Single Leg Stiff Leg Deadlift
Plate Good Morning
steps: Stand with feet hip-width apart, the plate held behind the neck and the knees slightly bent.
Bend forward at the hips, keeping the back straight, until the torso is parallel to the floor.
Push through the hips to return to the starting position.
